page.title: 05Birds of the Fens
page.content: We went out to{Farcet Fen}to see what birds we could observe.We looked through the binoculars.We saw a dove, a skylark,a wagtail and two thrushes. Later on we saw a swift, a blackbird, a green-finch and some starlings. It is quite common to see pheasants and pigeons feeding on the crops in the fields and sometimes it is possible to see a partridge.Herons, mute swans and Canada geese visit this area and the black headed gull can be seen quite often. Crows,rooks.linnets,great-tits, song-thrushes and sparrows are either resident,or frequent visitors. On the way back to school we saw a kestrel hovering over the fields.
